# Error Message Templates for User-Friendly Display

## Connection Errors
CONNECTION_FAILED=Unable to connect to sync server. Please check:\n‚Ä¢ Server is running\n‚Ä¢ Network connectivity\n‚Ä¢ Firewall settings\n‚Ä¢ Server address is correct
WEBSOCKET_DISCONNECTED=Lost connection to sync server. Attempting to reconnect...
DISCOVERY_FAILED=Network discovery found no servers.\n\nTry:\n‚Ä¢ Manual IP entry\n‚Ä¢ Check firewall settings\n‚Ä¢ Ensure server is running\n‚Ä¢ Verify same network

## Configuration Errors
INVALID_SERVER_URL=Invalid server address format.\n\nExpected: ws://SERVER_IP:8080/sync\nExample: ws://192.168.1.100:8080/sync
ENCRYPTION_KEY_MISMATCH=Encryption key mismatch. Ensure all devices use the same encryption key.
MISSING_JAVA=Java 17+ is required but not found.\n\nPlease install Java 17 or higher and try again.

## File and Content Errors
IMAGE_TOO_LARGE=Image too large for sync ({0} MB). Maximum size is {1} MB.\n\nTip: Large images are skipped to maintain performance.
CLIPBOARD_ACCESS_DENIED=Cannot access system clipboard.\n\nOn macOS: Grant accessibility permissions\nOn Linux: Ensure X11 clipboard support
FILE_NOT_FOUND=File not found: {0}\n\nThe file may have been moved or deleted.

## Network Errors
FIREWALL_BLOCKED=Connection blocked by firewall.\n\nPlease allow:\n‚Ä¢ Port 8080 (WebSocket)\n‚Ä¢ Port 8081 (Discovery)\n‚Ä¢ Java application through firewall
NETWORK_TIMEOUT=Network timeout occurred.\n\nCheck:\n‚Ä¢ Network connectivity\n‚Ä¢ Server is responsive\n‚Ä¢ No network interference
MULTICAST_NOT_SUPPORTED=Network doesn't support multicast discovery.\n\nUse manual server IP entry instead.

